SUMMARY:Volga Kama Mythologies: Mordva
DESCRIPTION:Event Details:    This four-part lecture series focuses on th
 e beliefs and mythologies of different ethnic minority groups across Russ
 ia\, with each program highlighting a different community.      This sess
 ion delves into the rich mythic traditions of the Mordva people\, explori
 ng their pantheon and the powerful role of women in their cosmology. This
  lecture highlights the "March of Feminism" within Mordva mythology\, whe
 re women rule the sky\, embodying strength\, wisdom\, and influence.     
  The session concludes with a musical performance of "Mordva Wedding"\, a
  piece that celebrates cultural rituals and the vibrancy of Mordva life. 
      This event is held in collaboration with faculty in the Slavic and E
 ast European Languages Department\, as well as the Jacobs School of Music
 .  Parking Information:Limited complimentary parking (https://nam12.safel
