X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p><strong>Event Details:</strong></p><div c
 lass="ewa-rteLine"><p class="ewa-rteLine">    This four-part lecture seri
 es focuses on the beliefs and mythologies of different ethnic minority gr
 oups across Russia\, with each program highlighting a different community
 .  </p><p class="">    This session delves into the rich mythic tradition
 s of the <strong>Mordva people</strong>\, exploring their pantheon and th
 e powerful role of women in their cosmology. This lecture highlights the 
 <strong>"March of Feminism"</strong> within Mordva mythology\, where <str
 ong>women rule the sky</strong>\, embodying strength\, wisdom\, and influ
 ence.  </p><p class="">    The session concludes with a musical performan
 ce of <strong>"Mordva Wedding"</strong>\, a piece that celebrates cultura
 l rituals and the vibrancy of Mordva life.  </p><p class="ewa-rteLine">  
   This event is held in collaboration with faculty in the Slavic and East
  European Languages Department\, as well as the Jacobs School of Music.  
 </p><div class="ewa-rteLine"></div></div><div class="ewa-rteLine"></div><
